Description: Faience stamp, or pill-making implement, with regular series of semicircular grooves on both sides, each side has regular series, of different size to those on the other side. Glaze surface remains in grooves - maroon colour. Core fine, creamy colour, close textured.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (TI.07)
Acquisition notes: Registered in 1909 with comment that 'found in Museum, many objects from Naukratis, some from Ephesus.' Not published by Petrie, Gardner or Hogarth
